2.5   Anatomical Position of the Heart in situ II
It is also helpful to further imagine that the heart has been rotated to the left, and because of this, the right side of the heart is turned toward the front of the body.
LOOK at the heart in the thorax;

its anterior surface is facing you. Note that its anterior surface is made up largely of the right ventricle. Palpate the following:
the right pulmonary surface; it is made up largely of the right atrium.  
 the left pulmonary surface; it is made up largely of the left ventricle.  
the diaphragmatic surface, by sliding your hand inferior to the heart. It is made up largely of the left ventricle, with a smaller contribution from the right ventricle.
